The paper deals with the study of random structures, specifically graphs, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The focus on properties that are true for most elements of a subset of graphs suggests a connection to Graph Theory (cs.GT). The development of tools to work with independence without assuming it may be relevant to Statistical Inference (cs.SI) and Network Science (cs.NE). Finally, the use of measures and approximation techniques suggests a connection to Information Theory (cs.IT).
